The '''torrent-lark''' ('''''Grallina bruijnii''''') is a species of [[bird]] in the family [[Monarchidae]] found on [[New Guinea]]. Its natural [[habitat]]s are subtropical or tropical moist lowland [[forest]]s and subtropical or tropical moist [[montane forest]].

Though most Monarchidae birds make their nests out of plant materials, the torrent-lark makes its nest out of mud.<ref>{{Cite journal |last1=Perez |first1=Daniela M. |last2=Gardner |first2=Janet L. |last3=Medina |first3=Iliana |date=2020-12-03 |title=Climate as an Evolutionary Driver of Nest Morphology in Birds: A Review |journal=Frontiers in Ecology and Evolution |volume=8 |doi=10.3389/fevo.2020.566018 |doi-access=free |issn=2296-701X|hdl=1885/283998 |hdl-access=free }}</ref>

